    "narrative": "The LawDog analytics department is prioritizing **Tyler Freeman** as today\u2019s cornerstone play. With a score of 68.67, **Tyler Freeman** benefits from a high-leverage matchup against Randy V\u00e1squez, whose 5.43 xERA is the most exploitable mark on the board. His assumed role in the two-hole provides the optimal environment for him to capitalize on his contact profile, and we are aggressively slotting him in for potential stolen base production given our organizational emphasis on speed. **Gleyber Torres** also warrants a strong recommendation at 51.25; while his platoon splits against right-handed pitching like Abel usually stifle his upside, his favorable spot in the two-hole and the pitcher\u2019s mediocre 4.28 xERA keep him firmly above our marginal threshold.\n\nThe margins are significantly tighter for **Gavin Sheets** and **Geraldo Perdomo**. **Gavin Sheets** sits at a 48.57, teetering on the edge of our starting requirements; he is essentially a neutral play today, though his expected fourth-spot billing offers enough stability to keep him active. Conversely, **Geraldo Perdomo** presents the most risk at 42.63. His efficiency is dragged down significantly by the tough matchup against McLean (3.04 xERA), which essentially negates any benefit derived from his position in the three-hole. While **Lawrence Butler** was the most notable bench consideration, his projected spot at the bottom of the order and the disadvantageous platoon against Weathers effectively closed the door on his inclusion, keeping him in the reserve pool for a more favorable series. \n\nWe are monitoring the lineup statuses for both **Gavin Sheets** and **Tyler Freeman** closely. Should their confirmed batting orders shift downward, we may see a regression in their efficiency scores that would force a re-evaluation of the daily cap strategy. With **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, and **Yainer Diaz** all unavailable due to scheduled off-days, our depth remains restricted. We are looking for **Bryson Stott**, **Will Smith**, **Taylor Ward**, **Matt Chapman**, **Daulton Varsho**, **Luis Arraez**, **Masyn Winn**, **Jonathan Aranda**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Wenceel Perez**, and **Drew Gilbert** to remain healthy and prepared to cycle into the rotation as the schedule dictates over the coming weekend.",
